parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause exhaust leaks into the passenger compartment, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning, which can be fatal.
symptoms: Unusual noises or smells from the exhaust system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo-charger oil seal can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage, decreased performance, and potentially causing engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The coolant leak can cause a short circuit, leading to an electrical fire, which can spread quickly and cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window switches can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may lead to water intrusion or other safety issues if the windows are stuck in an open or closed position.
symptoms: power windows get stuck in an open or closed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview mirror mounting brackets can cause the mirror to fall off, obstructing the driver's view and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: rearview mirror is difficult to adjust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The water leaks in the air conditioning/heater core can cause coolant to short circuit the fuse box, leading to electrical system failures, and potentially causing accidents or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering fluid return hose can cause hydraulic oil to spray on the hot engine, leading to a fire hazard, and compromise directional control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations while steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the steering rack mounting rubbers can affect the directional control of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents, and lead to premature wear of other steering components.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations while steering
